  "description": "Found by \"bzzzzrt\" call so different from that given by WEME. I really could not describe bird better than it is shown in photos. The white pattern on tail fits Eastern juv better than Western juv (see discussion and photos of specimens at\u00a0https://www.flickr.com/photos/36088296@N08/albums/72157658379567708.\n\r\nThe lack of dark along veins of tail feathers would strongly indicate liliana subspecies.\u00a0\n\r\nThe extensive dark on uppertail coverts was visible in field, as was contrasty head (more so than many nearby WEME). The throat was distinctly yellow and malars entirely white.",
